<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - TROUBLESHOOTING - BRAKE DRAG</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BRAKE DRAG</title>
        <table id="t0401705" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CONDITION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">POSSIBLE CAUSE</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CORRECTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="4" align="center">
                            <para>All four brakes drag.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Calipers binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Repair or replace calipers.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Hydro-Max&#8482; booster partially self applying.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Repair or replace power steering pump. Replace pedal, pedal bushings or pedal pin,
                                if necessary.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Brake pedal not fully returning.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Repair cause of brake pedal not returning.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Malfunctioning master cylinder, trapping pressure at the calipers. (See note at end
                                of table 5).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Malfunctioning ABS HCU, trapping pressure at all calipers.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5. Repair or replace HCU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="3">
                            <para>Both brakes on one axle drag.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Calipers binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Repair or replace calipers.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Hose or brake line to this axle restricted.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Locate restriction, replace appropriate parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Malfunctioning ABS HCU, trapping pressure at these calipers.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Repair or replace HCU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Malfunctioning Hydro-Max&#8482; booster, preventing master cylinder from
                                releasing.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="2">
                            <para>Single brake drags.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Calipers binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Repair or replace calipers.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Hose or brake line to this brake restricted.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Locate restriction, replace appropriate parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Malfunctioning ABS HCU, trapping pressure at this brake caliper.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Repair or replace ABS HCU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN2">
                            <note>
                                <para>A common cause of a malfunctioning master cylinder is swollen seals due to putting
                                    the wrong fluid (usually power steering fluid) into the master cylinder. This is
                                    easily detectable. The diaphragms inside the fill caps of the reservoir will be
                                    swollen. If the diaphragms are swollen, the master cylinder must be replaced. Also,
                                    the calipers must be examined for swollen seals. If the caliper seals are swollen,
                                    the calipers must be repaired or replaced. Also, the brake hoses may be damaged and
                                    weakened. They should be replaced. Finally, the brake lines should be flushed with
                                    clean brake fluid until clean brake fluid comes through each of the bleeder screws
                                    at the calipers.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
